Description: Fragment of of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Astymedes. Perhaps from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 039.50. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 32, 25
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1069)
